No results found













                    		The family of  bleach 






















How to use Clorox® Regular-Bleach1





Cleaning, Sanitizing & Disinfecting




Bathroom












Toilets



Toilets

To Clean and Disinfect a toilet bowl: Flush toilet or bidet. Pour ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 into bowl. Brush bowl with scrub brush and let stand for 10 minutes. Flush.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Bathtubs



Bathtubs

To Clean and Disinfect: Pre-wash surface with clean water. Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Sinks



Sinks

To Clean and Disinfect:  Pre-wash surface. Wipe with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Faucets



Faucets

To Clean and Disinfect:  Pre-wash surface. Wipe with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Tile



Tile

To Clean and Disinfect:  Pre-wash surface. Wipe or mop area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Plastic Bath Toys



Plastic Bath Toys

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Soak prewashed toys 5 minutes. Rinse well and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.





Name of item clicked below










Nursery












Potty Chairs



Potty Chairs

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Empty seat and fill with bleach solution. Let stand for 5 minutes. Rinse, drain and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Plastic Toys



Plastic Toys

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Soak pre-washed toys 5 minutes. Rinse and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




High Chairs



High Chairs

To Clean and Disinfect hard, nonporous surfaces: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Sponge down pre-washed surface and let stand 5 minutes. Rinse and let air dry. *Safe for hard, nonporous surfaces only.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Changing Tables



Changing Tables

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½  cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Sponge down prewashed surface and let stand 5 minutes. Rinse and let air dry. *Safe for hard, nonporous surfaces only.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Baby Bottles



Baby Bottles

To Clean and Sanitize: Mix 2 tsp. of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Soak pre-washed baby bottles for 2 minutes. Rinse well and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.





Name of item clicked below










Kitchen












Floors



Floors

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe or mop area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry.To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Disposals



Disposals

To Clean and Disinfect: pour ¾ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 into drain while running disposal and water.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Sippy Cups



Sippy Cups

To Clean & Sanitize: Mix 2 tsp of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Soak pre-washed cups for 2 minutes. Drain and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Plastic Cutting Boards



Plastic Cutting Boards

To Clean and Sanitize: Mix 2 tbsp. of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Pour solution over pre-washed cutting board and let stand for 2 minutes. Rinse with 2 tsp of this product per gallon of water. Do not rinse or soak overnight.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Appliances



Appliances

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Countertops



Countertops

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry. *Safe for hard, nonporous surfaces only.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Sinks



Sinks

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Faucets



Faucets

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Garbage Cans



Garbage Cans

To Clean: Pre-wash surface. Wipe area with a solution of ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. To Sanitize: Wash, rinse and wipe surface area with a solution of 2 teaspoons of bleach per 1 gallon of water for (at least) 2 minutes. Let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.





Name of item clicked below










Any Room












Travel Mugs & Water Bottles



Travel Mugs & Water Bottles

To Clean and Sanitize: Mix 2 tsp. of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Pre-wash surface. Fill pre-washed travel mugs and water bottles and let stand 2 minutes. Drain and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Appliances



Appliances

To Clean and Disinfect: Pre-wash surface with clean water. Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 into 1 gallon of water. Wipe surface with bleach solution and let stand for 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Walls



Walls

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Pre-wash surface. Wipe with bleach solution and let stand for 5 minutes. Rinse and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Pet Bowls



Pet Bowls

To Clean and Sanitize: Mix 2 tsp of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Pre-wash surface. Fill prewashed bowls and let stand 2 minutes. Drain and air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




Light Switches



Light Switches

To Clean and Disinfect: Mix ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 per gallon of water. Prewash surface. Wipe surface with bleach solution and let stand for 5 minutes. Rinse and let air dry.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.





Name of item clicked below










Emergency Water Disinfection












Emergency Water Disinfection



Emergency Water Disinfection

When boiling off water for 1 minute is not practical, water can be made potable by using this product. Prior to addition of the sanitizer, remove suspended material by filtration or by allowing it to settle to the bottom. Decant the clarified contaminated water into a clean container and add 8 drops to 1 gallon of water (2 drops to 1 quart) or add 1/8 teaspoon of this product to 1½ gallons of water. Allow the treated water to stand for 30 minutes. Properly treated water will have a slight chlorine odor. If not, repeat dosage and allow the water to stand an additional 15 minutes. The treated water can then be made palatable by pouring it between clean containers several times.
For cloudy water, use 16 drops per 1 gallon of water (4 drops to 1 quart) or add 1/4 teaspoon of this product per 1½ gallons of water. If no chlorine odor is apparent after 30 minutes, repeat dosage and wait an additional 15 minutes.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.





Name of item clicked below
















Doing Laundry




Whites












Dirt Stains



Dirt Stains

To Remove Stains and Clean: If bleach dispenser is available, fill to the maximum level. Add laundry. If you don't have a dispenser, for best results add ½ cup Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 5 minutes after the wash cycle has begun. To Sanitize: Add ½ cup of Clorox® Regular-Bleach1 to a standard-size washer following the laundry use directions.






*Always read and follow precautions and usage directions before using cleaning products. Store out of reach of children.




